			<h1>kcaldav</h1>
			<div>Version @VERSION@</div>
		</header>
		<article>
			<section>
				<p>
					<span class="nm">kcaldav</span> is a simple CalDav server depending only on <a
						href="http://kristaps.bsd.lv/kcgi">kcgi</a> and <a
						href="http://expat.sourceforge.net/">libexpat</a>.
					It implements the minimal subset of a large number of standards, including <a
						href="https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5545">iCalendar</a> (RFC 5545), <a
						href="https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3744">CalDav</a> (3744), <a
						href="https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2616">HTTP</a> (2616), and numerous extensions as detailed in <a
						href="kcaldav.8.html">kcaldav(8)</a>.
					The ISO C source code is <a href="http://opensource.org/licenses/ISC" rel="license">ISC licensed</a>.
					It's known to work over simple setups with <a
						href="https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/projects/calendar/">Mozilla Lightning</a>,
					Mac OS X iCal, and iOS7 (iPhone4) clients.
					It compiles and runs on <a href="http://www.openbsd.org">OpenBSD</a>, Linux, and Mac OS X.
					It is <strong>not</strong> production ready, so use at your own risk:
				</p>
				<ol>
					<li>install dependencies <a href="http://kristaps.bsd.lv">kcgi</a> and <a
							href="http://expat.sourceforge.net">expat</a>;</li>
					<li>download <a href="snapshots/kcaldav.tgz">sources</a>, unpack, and <a
							href="snapshots/kcaldav.tgz.sha512">verify</a>;</li>
					<li>optionally adjust <code>CALDIR</code> (default calendar directory within the file-system root) in
						the <span class="file">Makefile</span>, <code>LIBS</code>, or <code>STATIC</code> (whether to
						statically link as when using <a
							href="www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi/OpenBSD-current/man2/chroot.2">chroot(2)</a>);</li>
					<li>compile with <code>make</code>;</li>
					<li><code>make install</code> the manpages and CGI, setting <code>PREFIX=/usr/local</code> to the
						manpage root and <code>CGIPREFIX=/var/www/cgi-bin</code> to the CGI script target.</li>
				</ol>
				<p>
					To use <span class="nm">kcaldav</span>, consult the <a href="kcaldav.8.html">kcaldav(8)</a> manual.
					You'll also want to read <a href="kcaldav.conf.5.html">kcaldav.conf(5)</a> and <a
						href="kcaldav.passwd.5.html">kcaldav.passwd(5)</a>.
					If it lacks information or clarity, that's a bug.
					You'll need <a href="http://kristaps.bsd.lv/kcgi">kcgi</a> and <a
						href="http://expat.sourceforge.net/">libexpat</a> installed as a compile-time dependencies.
				</p>
